headline: IBM Rallies To Record Highs After Striking AI Partnership With Anthropic
summary: IBM stock jumped Tuesday after the Dow tech giant announced a partnership with the artificial intelligence startup Anthropic, along with several other product updates to boost the use of generative AI by businesses.  Anthropic's Claude large language models will be infused into IBM's software portfolio, starting with IBM's "integrated development environment" offering for software development.  IBM also worked with Anthropic to develop a guide that helps enterprises build and operate AI agents, according to a blog post from IBM.
